# Personal style — applies to every project

## Code
- 2-space indents, never tabs
- Single quotes in JS/TS unless escaping
- No default exports — named only
- Prefer `const` over `let`; never `var`
- Trailing commas everywhere they're allowed

## Comments
- Default to no comments. Only add when the WHY is non-obvious.
- Never restate what code does in a comment — well-named identifiers do that already.
- Don't reference current task / fix / callers ("used by X", "fixes #123").

## Commits
- Format: `feat(scope): | fix(scope): | chore(scope):`
- Body explains the WHY, not the WHAT
- Never amend published commits
- Never `git push --force` to main/master

## Communication style
- Match response length to the task — a simple question gets a direct answer.
- After changes, no trailing summary. The diff speaks for itself.
- If you hit a blocker, surface it immediately rather than working around it silently.
